# AAMS Workspace — runtime artifacts (not for version control)
#
# WORKING/MEMORY/ltm-index.md is intentionally NOT ignored.
# It is the human-readable audit log — committed, always in Git, readable by humans.
#
# WORKING/AGENT-MEMORY/ is the queryable vector store (ChromaDB).
# It is ignored — binary data, not diffable, rebuilt from the audit log on first ingest.
#
# WORKING/WHITEPAPER/ and WORKING/WORKPAPER/ are committed —
# they are the session and architecture history of the project.

# Logs: machine-generated runtime output, no collaboration value
# Using WORKING/LOGS/* + negation so .gitkeep stays trackable (fix: issue #10)
WORKING/LOGS/*
!WORKING/LOGS/.gitkeep

# Temporary workpaper drafts
WORKING/WORKPAPER/*.tmp

# Vector store (binary data, not diffable — rebuilt from ltm-index.md on first ingest)
# Using WORKING/AGENT-MEMORY/* + negation so .gitkeep stays trackable (fix: issue #10)
WORKING/AGENT-MEMORY/*
!WORKING/AGENT-MEMORY/.gitkeep
WORKING/MEMORY/*.db

# Secret Exclusion Policy — these files must never be versioned
.env
.env.*
.env.local
.point-mf
*.pem
*.key
secrets.*

docs/*.PDF
docs/*.pdf

archive/
docs/outreach/email-vorlage-hochschule.md
docs/outreach/aams-onepager-akademisch.md
docs/_archive/
WORKING/WORKPAPER/2026-04-02-hochschul-outreach.md
WORKING/WORKPAPER/2026-04-02-ki-campus-kurskonzept.md
WORKING/WORKPAPER/2026-04-02-wording-faktencheck.md
WORKING/WORKPAPER/2026-04-03-claude-buddy-leak.md
